{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ApnVmEDSi88AA7Rq7LGZza","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary with all the information I've gathered. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary: Runs Page and Run Listing/Display Code\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the Cloche codebase, here's everything related to the Runs page, run listing, and sorting logic:\n\n### 1. **Web UI Handlers** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**Main Runs Page Handler:**\n- **Function:** `handleRunsList` (lines 230-276)\n  - Supports filtering by project via query parameter `?project=<dir>`\n  - Fetches runs from store using `ListRuns()` or `ListRunsByProject()`\n  - Passes runs to template for rendering\n  - Also collects retained container counts per project\n\n**Project Runs Redirect:**\n- **Function:** `handleProjectRuns` (lines 278-285)\n  - Redirects `/projects/{name}/runs` to `/runs?project=<dir>`\n\n**API JSON Endpoint:**\n- **Function:** `handleAPIRuns` (lines 458-483)\n  - Returns JSON array of runs\n  - Converts domain.Run to apiRun struct with formatted fields\n  - Supports same project filtering as HTML handler\n\n### 2. **Run Type Definition** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, lines 31-47)\n\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState              // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time             // KEY SORTING FIELD\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string\n    IsHost         bool                  // host vs container run\n    ParentRunID    string                // for parent-child relationships\n}\n```\n\n**RunState Constants:**\n- `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n\n### 3. **Database Sorting** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\n**Primary Sorting:** All runs are sorted by `started_at DESC` (most recent first) at the database level:\n\n**ListRuns (lines 193-209):**\n```sql\nSELECT ... FROM runs ORDER BY started_at DESC\n```\n\n**ListRunsByProject (lines 224-241):**\n```sql\nSELECT ... FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? ORDER BY started_at DESC\n```\n\n**ListChildRuns (lines 262-271):**\n```sql\nSELECT ... FROM runs WHERE parent_run_id = ? ORDER BY started_at ASC\n(Note: Child runs sorted ascending by start time)\n```\n\n**Query Columns (line 144):**\n```\nid, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, \nerror_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id\n```\n\n### 4. **Template/Frontend Display** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`)\n\n**HTML Table Rendering (lines 14-47):**\n- Table columns: Run ID, Title, Project, Workflow, Type, State, Timing, Container, Error\n- Displays runs in order received from backend\n\n**JavaScript Grouping Logic (lines 64-107):**\n- `groupRuns()` function organizes runs to display child runs directly after their parent\n- Handles orphaned children (parents not in current view)\n- Deemphasizes parent rows; highlights children as \"active work\"\n\n**Real-time Polling (lines 109-161):**\n- `poll()` function fetches `/api/runs` every 3 seconds\n- Reorders results using `groupRuns()`\n- Dynamically updates table body\n\n**Row Classes:**\n- `run-parent-row` - for host/parent runs\n- `run-child-row` - for child/container runs\n\n### 5. **gRPC Service** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 367-391)\n\n**ListRuns RPC:**\n- Takes `ListRunsRequest` with `All` boolean flag\n- If `All` is false: filters to last 1 hour (`since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)`)\n- If `All` is true: returns all runs\n- Converts domain.Run to `RunSummary` protobuf\n\n### 6. **CLI List Command** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 204-242)\n\n**cmdList function:**\n- Supports `--all` flag (default: last hour only)\n- Calls gRPC `ListRuns` endpoint\n- Displays runs in order received with formatted output\n- Shows: RunID, WorkflowName, State, Type, Title, ContainerID, ErrorMessage\n\n### 7. **Formatting Functions** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`, lines 1376-1401)\n\n**formatRunTiming:**\n- **Running:** \"5m\" (duration only)\n- **Completed:** \"20m, 1 hour ago\" (duration + relative time)\n- **Pending:** \"\" (empty)\n\n### 8. **Proto Definitions** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n\n**ListRunsRequest (lines 88-90):**\n```protobuf\nmessage ListRunsRequest {\n  bool all = 1;  // if false: last hour only\n}\n```\n\n**RunSummary (lines 96-105):**\n```protobuf\nmessage RunSummary {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string workflow_name = 2;\n  string state = 3;\n  string started_at = 4;     // KEY SORTING FIELD (raw format)\n  string error_message = 5;\n  string container_id = 6;\n  string title = 7;\n  bool is_host = 8;\n}\n```\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Main page handlers, API endpoints, formatting |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` | Runs page template with client-side grouping |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Database queries with `ORDER BY started_at DESC` |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run struct definition with StartedAt/CompletedAt fields |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC ListRuns implementation |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI list command |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | Proto definitions for ListRuns RPC |\n\n### Sorting Summary\n\n**Primary Sort:** `started_at DESC` (most recent first) - applied at database query level\n- All runs are sorted by when they 