{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017NzUtKpP1Kw9RE4xzzHSBa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package domain\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"strings\"\n     5→\t\"time\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→type RunState string\n     9→\n    10→const (\n    11→\tRunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    12→\tRunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    13→\tRunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    14→\tRunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    15→\tRunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n    16→)\n    17→\n    18→type StepExecution struct {\n    19→\tStepName    string\n    20→\tResult      string\n    21→\tStartedAt   time.Time\n    22→\tCompletedAt time.Time\n    23→\tLogs        string\n    24→\tGitRef      string // output state\n    25→}\n    26→\n    27→func (e *StepExecution) Duration() time.Duration {\n    28→\treturn e.CompletedAt.Sub(e.StartedAt)\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→type Run struct {\n    32→\tID             string\n    33→\tWorkflowName   string\n    34→\tState          RunState\n    35→\tActiveSteps    []string\n    36→\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    37→\tStartedAt      time.Time\n    38→\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n    39→\tProjectDir     string\n    40→\tErrorMessage   string\n    41→\tContainerID    string\n    42→\tBaseSHA        string // Git HEAD at run start, for result branch creation\n    43→\tContainerKept  bool   // true when the container was retained after run completion\n    44→\tTitle          string // One-line summary of the work being done\n    45→\tIsHost         bool   // true for host workflow runs (vs container runs)\n    46→\tParentRunID    string // ID of the parent (host) run, empty for top-level runs\n    47→}\n    48→\n    49→func NewRun(id, workflowName string) *Run {\n    50→\treturn &Run{\n    51→\t\tID:           id,\n    52→\t\tWorkflowName: workflowName,\n    53→\t\tState:        RunStatePending,\n    54→\t}\n    55→}\n    56→\n    57→func (r *Run) Start() {\n    58→\tr.State = RunStateRunning\n    59→\tr.StartedAt = time.Now()\n    60→}\n    61→\n    62→func (r *Run) RecordStepStart(stepName string) {\n    63→\tr.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps, stepName)\n    64→\tr.StepExecutions = append(r.StepExecutions, &StepExecution{\n    65→\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n    66→\t\tStartedAt: time.Now(),\n    67→\t})\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→func (r *Run) RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string) {\n    71→\t// Remove from active steps\n    72→\tfor i, name := range r.ActiveSteps {\n    73→\t\tif name == stepName {\n    74→\t\t\tr.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps[:i], r.ActiveSteps[i+1:]...)\n    75→\t\t\tbreak\n    76→\t\t}\n    77→\t}\n    78→\t// Mark execution complete\n    79→\tfor i := len(r.StepExecutions) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n    80→\t\tif r.StepExecutions[i].StepName == stepName && r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt.IsZero() {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e7ed9f0-b7c4-40c4-97b1-03db40146cc3","uuid":"02fd7afb-eada-4625-9e11-da67c94b041b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/domain/run.go","content":"package domain\n\nimport (\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n\tRunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n\tRunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n\tRunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n\tRunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n\tRunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n\tStepName    string\n\tResult      string\n\tStartedAt   time.Time\n\tCompletedAt time.Time\n\tLogs        string\n\tGitRef      string // output state\n}\n\nfunc (e *StepExecution) Duration() time.Duration {\n\treturn e.CompletedAt.Sub(e.StartedAt)\n}\n\ntype Run struct {\n\tID             string\n\tWorkflowName   string\n\tState          RunState\n\tActiveSteps    []string\n\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n\tStartedAt      time.Time\n\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n\tProjectDir     string\n\tErrorMessage   string\n\tContainerID    string\n\tBaseSHA        string // Git HEAD at run start, for result branch creation\n\tContainerKept  bool   // true when the container was retained after run completion\n\tTitle          string // One-line summary of the work being done\n\tIsHost         bool   // true for host workflow runs (vs container runs)\n\tParentRunID    string // ID of the parent (host) run, empty for top-level runs\n}\n\nfunc NewRun(id, workflowName string) *Run {\n\treturn &Run{\n\t\tID:           id,\n\t\tWorkflowName: workflowName,\n\t\tState:        RunStatePending,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (r *Run) Start() {\n\tr.State = RunStateRunning\n\tr.StartedAt = time.Now()\n}\n\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepStart(stepName string) {\n\tr.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps, stepName)\n\tr.StepExecutions = append(r.StepExecutions, &StepExecution{\n\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n\t\tStartedAt: time.Now(),\n\t})\n}\n\nfunc (r *Run) RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string) {\n\t// Remove from active steps\n\tfor i, name := range r.ActiveSteps {\n\t\tif name == stepName {\n\t\t\tr.ActiveSteps = append(r.ActiveSteps[:i], r.ActiveSteps[i+1:]...)\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t// Mark execution complete\n\tfor i := len(r.StepExecutions) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n\t\tif r.StepExecutions[i].StepName == stepName && r.StepExecutions[i].CompletedAt.IsZero() {","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":113}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QHs8wnnUrhchEnxNdMAmsS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The best approach is to change the SQL `ORDER BY` clause to sort running runs first, then by `started_at DESC`. This is the cleanest approach because:\n\n1. It affects both the initial page load (server-side template) and the API endpoint used for polling\n2. The `groupRuns()` JavaScript function preserves relative order within top-level runs\n\nLet me also check the `ListChildRuns` - for child runs, the ordering should probably also put running first, then by time ascending (since children are sorted ascending).\n\nActually, let me think about the `groupRuns()` function more carefully. It:\n\n\n- Separates runs into parents and children\n- Inserts each parent's children right after it in the list\n- Appends any orphaned children at the end\n\nSince the relative order of top-level runs is preserved from the API response, sorting at the database level means the top-level runs will already be ordered correctly: running first, then by time. The children within each parent group will maintain their API response order, and the parent's position in the list determines where its children appear.\n\nThe parent-child grouping should take precedence over the running-first sorting. Looking at the requirements again, I need to sort the Runs pages to put running status runs at the top, then by time—and this applies to the top-level ordering. The `groupRuns` function handles the parent-child grouping, but within the top-level runs, running ones should come first.\n\nI think the cleanest approach is to update the SQL ORDER BY clause to prioritize running state first, then sort by time, and also handle this in the JavaScript `groupRuns` function to maintain the sorting through the grouping logic.\n\nActually, the `groupRuns` function just groups without sorting—it preserves the API response order for top-level runs. So if the database returns running runs first, that order flows through to the frontend. I should focus on the SQL changes in `ListRuns` and `ListRunsByProject` to use a CASE statement that puts running state at priority 0 and everything else at priority 1, then sorts by started_at descending. The task specifies only \"running\" gets this treatment, not pending or other states.\n\nNow I need to verify whether the API endpoint uses the same store methods, and then write a test to confirm the sorting works correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5399,"cache_read_input_tokens":16381,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5399},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e7ed9f0-b7c4-40c4-97b1-03db40146cc3","uuid":"c020e253-e65d-4d20-97d5-add596e53fac"}
